"title": "1210: God, human descriptions of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1210: god, human descriptions of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Figures of speech which describe God in human terms, sometimes referred to as anthropomorphisms. Since God is Spirit, these expressions help the human mind to understand God, and enable God to reveal himself to human beings.</p>\n<h2>Bodily form ascribed to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:23\">EXO 33:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:2-Gen18:14\">GEN 18:2–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:13-Josh5:15\">JOS 5:13–5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:26-Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:26–1:28</a></p>\n<h3>His face</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:25-Num6:26\">NUM 6:25–6:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:8\">PSA 27:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:9\">PSA 51:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:10\">MAT 18:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:4\">REV 22:4</a></p>\n<h3>His heart</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:16\">2CH 7:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6\">GEN 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:21\">GEN 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:14\">1SA 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:22\">ACT 13:22</a></p>\n<h3>His hands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:27\">ISA 14:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:19\">1CH 28:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:14\">1CH 29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:16\">1CH 29:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:4\">PSA 45:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33-Acts2:34\">ACT 2:33–2:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:6\">1PE 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>His eyes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:9\">2CH 16:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:12\">DEU 11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:3\">PRO 15:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:8\">AMO 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:10\">ZEC 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:12\">1PE 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:15\">PSA 34:15</a></p>\n<h3>His feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:7\">EZK 43:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:3\">DEU 33:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:10\">2SA 22:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:9\">PSA 18:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:5\">PSA 45:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:13\">ISA 60:13</a></p>\n<h3>His arm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1\">ISA 59:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:21\">JER 32:21</a></strong> <em>God's arm is particularly used as a symbol of his power at the exodus.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6\">EXO 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:15\">DEU 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:9\">JOB 40:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:9\">ISA 51:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:10\">ISA 52:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:5\">ISA 63:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:51\">LUK 1:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:38\">JHN 12:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:1\">ISA 53:1</a></p>\n<h3>His mind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:34\">ROM 11:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:13\">ISA 40:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:29\">1SA 15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:31\">JER 7:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:21\">HEB 7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:4\">PSA 110:4</a></p>\n<h2>Human actions ascribed to God</h2>\n<h3>He walks</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8\">GEN 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a></p>\n<h3>He speaks</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:12\">DEU 4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:6\">JOB 40:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:3-Ps29:9\">PSA 29:3–29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:9\">PSA 33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:24\">EZK 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:6\">ACT 7:6</a></p>\n<h3>He rests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2\">GEN 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:11\">EXO 20:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:4\">HEB 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>He rides</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:4\">PSA 68:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:26\">DEU 33:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:11\">2SA 22:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:10\">PSA 18:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:33\">PSA 68:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:8\">HAB 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>He laughs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:8\">PSA 59:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:4\">PSA 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:13\">PSA 37:13</a></p>\n<h3>Other actions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:26\">ISA 5:26</a> <em>God whistles</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a> <em>God knocks</em></p>\n<h2>Human senses ascribed to God</h2>\n<h3>He hears</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:3\">PSA 4:3</a></strong> <em>God's hearing usually refers to his answering of prayer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:11\">GEN 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:9\">PSA 94:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:13\">LUK 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:42\">JHN 11:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7\">HEB 5:7</a></p>\n<h3>He sees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:13\">GEN 16:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:4\">GEN 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:7\">2CH 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:9\">NEH 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:18\">PRO 24:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:12-Ezek8:13\">EZK 8:12–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:10\">JON 3:10</a></p>\n<h3>He smells</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:21\">GEN 8:21</a></strong> <em>God's smelling refers to his acceptance of sacrifices.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:9\">LEV 1:9</a></p>\n<h2>God experiences emotion</h2>\n<h3>He shows delight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:17\">ZEP 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:9\">DEU 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:4\">PSA 149:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:7\">ISA 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:4\">ISA 62:4</a></p>\n<h3>He is compassionate</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:11\">JAS 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:9\">PSA 145:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:10\">ISA 54:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:19\">HOS 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8\">HOS 11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3\">2CO 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>He is angry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:10-Ps95:11\">PSA 95:10–95:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:11\">2KI 17:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:58\">PSA 78:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:29\">PSA 106:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:25\">ISA 5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:8\">ISA 54:8</a></p>\n<h3>He experiences pain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6\">GEN 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:35\">1SA 15:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:16\">2SA 24:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:15\">1CH 21:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek6:9\">EZK 6:9</a></p>\n<h2>Human occupations ascribed to God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:16\">ISA 29:16</a></strong> <em>God as a potter.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:3\">EXO 15:3</a> <em>God as a warrior</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:1\">PSA 23:1</a> <em>God as a shepherd</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:10\">HEB 11:10</a> <em>God as a builder</em></p>\n<h2>Human relationships ascribed to God</h2>\n<h3>God as a loving husband</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5-Isa54:8\">ISA 54:5–54:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:14\">JER 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:16\">HOS 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>God as a loving father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:13\">PSA 103:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:2-Isa1:3\">ISA 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:9\">JER 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1-Hos11:4\">HOS 11:1–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:27\">MAT 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:27\">JHN 16:27</a></p>\n<h2>God is not to be brought down to human levels</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:9\">HOS 11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:32\">JOB 9:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:21\">PSA 50:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:8-Isa55:9\">ISA 55:8–55:9</a></p>",
